subSubSection.paragraph:
Chaetiger 1 with well-developed capillary chaetae and small postchaetal lamellae in both rami; notopodial lamellae triangular; neuropodial lamellae rounded.All notopodia with capillary chaetae only. Low prechaetal lamellae present in noto- and neuropodia on anterior chaetigers after chaetiger 1. Notopodial postchaetal lamellae large, leaf-like on branchiate chaetigers, usually largest on chaetiger 4, not overlapping middorsally, greatly diminishing in size on posterior abranchiate chaetigers; lamellae on at least ten anterior chaetigers with terminal acute peaks on upper tips (
Fig. 6A, C–E, G
). Neuropodial postchaetal lamellae ear-like on branchiate chaetigers, greatly diminishing in size on posterior abranchiate chaetigers.

