subSubSection.paragraph:
Pygidium with up to eleven pairs of cirri (seven pairs in 
holotype
) arranged around terminal anus, comprising one pair of ventral cirri and up to ten pairs of thinner and longer dorsal cirri; fewer cirri in small individuals.
